At 5am he climbed into his MG6 coupe and was spotted by police veering across the road close to the Weymouth and Portland National Sailing Academy.

A breath test showed he was more than twice the drink drive limit and Lee was fined and banned from driving for 18 months by magistrates in Weymouth. 

Hours later the South Korean Olympic delegation in London held an emergency disciplinary committee and decided to send the coach back to Seoul.

It was reported that the delegation believed Lee’s ‘reprehensible act’ would have had an adverse effect on the ‘honor and morale’ of the national team.

