Julian Lawrence, prosecuting, told magistrates that Lee’s manner of driving had aroused interest in the police.

He said: 'Though it was still dark the car’s headlights were not on and as police followed it they saw the vehicle was veering towards the road’s central white line.

'That gave them cause for concern.'

He said Lee had been on his own in the car and appeared unsteady on his feet when he got out of the vehicle.

