He was ordered to pay a fine and costs totalling £340 and was banned from driving in the UK for 18 months.

The latest controversy to hit the Games comes after the South Korea flag was displayed by mistake before the women's
Olympic soccer match between North Korea and Colombia in Glasgow on Wednesday.

The North Korean team walked off the pitch after the incident before being persuaded to return and start the game.

Greece's triple jumper Voula Papahristou is also going home after posting a racist tweet on Twitter.

Her offending message – which was referring to reports of mosquitoes carrying the West Nile virus in her home country – read: ‘With so many Africans in Greece, at least the West Nile mosquitoes will eat home made food!’

